%% Sequence Diagram — Error Scenario: Invalid Comparison Blocked
%% Import: Arrange → Insert → Mermaid → choose "Diagram"

sequenceDiagram
    title Error Scenario — Comparability Gate Blocks Invalid Comparison (Updated 2026-07-08)
    autonumber
    actor R as Researcher
    participant CLI as Orchestrator<br/>(Python CLI)
    participant ML as MLflow<br/>(local tracking)
    participant CG as Comparability Gate
    participant SC as Statistical Comparator<br/>(SciPy)

    R->>+CLI: bench compare run_a run_b
    CLI->>+ML: fetch metadata(run_a, run_b)
    ML-->>-CLI: params_a, params_b

    CLI->>+CG: validate_comparability(params_a, params_b)

    Note over CG: Check: prompt dataset hash match?
    Note over CG: Check: hardware profile match?
    Note over CG: Check: metrics schema version match?
    Note over CG: Check: thermal monitoring quality compatible?
    Note over CG: Check: OS/library versions compatible?

    alt Violations found
        CG-->>-CLI: BLOCKED — violations: [different prompt hash, degraded thermal on run_b]
        CLI-->>R: ❌ Comparison blocked.<br/>Violations:<br/>1. Prompt dataset hash mismatch<br/>2. Run B had degraded thermal monitoring<br/><br/>Re-run with matching conditions or acknowledge caveats.
    else All checks pass
        CG-->>CLI: COMPARABLE
        CLI->>+SC: compare(run_a_metrics, run_b_metrics)
        SC->>SC: Shapiro-Wilk normality test
        alt Normal distributions
            SC->>SC: Welch's t-test
        else Non-normal
            SC->>SC: Mann-Whitney U test
        end
        SC-->>-CLI: effect_size, CI_95, p_value, verdict
        CLI-->>-R: ✓ Statistically significant improvement of 12.3% ± 2.1% (p=0.003, Cohen's d=0.84)
    end
